headline: United Rentals (URI): Evaluating Value After Q3 Margin Pressures and Guidance Update
summary: United Rentals (URI) reported its third quarter results, sparking a pullback in the stock as earnings landed below market expectations. While revenue climbed on strong demand, investors focused on margin pressures impacting profitability. See our latest analysis for United Rentals. United Rentals’ share price has cooled recently, losing over 11% in the past month after a softer earnings report, but it is still up more than 26% year-to-date.
